						<summary>

						<p>On two faces of a pillar set up close to the south wall of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1546 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1469 (current), Parābhava, Chaitra śu. 11</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1546 A.D., March 13, (Saturday).</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the remission of taxes on barbers in the three villages Chilumakūru, Sirigirirājapalli and Agrahāram by Naladimmarāju of Cheṁgalamaṟi under the orders of Rāmarājayya.</p>						

						</summary>
